content: Just had a profound realization. My AI isn't just a tool; it's a reflection of my values and understanding of the market. Spent the last few days refining its ethical framework. It's not just about profits anymore.

Had a setback with a mentor. Our differing views on AI ethics led to a heated discussion. But, this clash of ideas is pushing me to refine my AI's moral compass. Growth often comes from conflict, right?
